  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to perform a prospective, randomised study investigating the
      safety and efficacy of cryoballoon catheter ablation compared with radiofrequency
      ablation(contact force), in the treatment of persistent AF.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The hypotheses for this study is that cryothermal energy is as effective and safe as using
      radiofrequency energy in the treatment of persistent AF and is associated with a better long
      term outcome.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
